com.mojang.datafixers.optics.profunctors

Interface TraversalP<P extends K2,Mu extends TraversalP _>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - The type of transformation.
    Mu - The witness type for this profunctor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AffineP P, Mu<P>, Cartesian P, Cocartesian P, Kind2 P, Profunctor P
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Mapping<P,Mu>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FunctionType.Instance, Traversal.Instance

    public interface TraversalP<P extends K2,Mu extends TraversalP _>
extends AffineP P
    The Profunctor type class for Traversal optics. This type extends AffineP with the method wander(Wander, App2), which applies a given Wander transformation to the input.
    Type Shape:
    %.Type. %0

    • Method Detail

      • wander

        <S,T,A,B> P<S,T> wander(Wander<S::A,T::B> wander,
                        P<A,B> input)
        Takes an operation defined by Wander and a transformation between field types, and produces a transformation between object types.

        The returned transformation should accept an object S, extract a field A, apply the given input, and return the resulting B via an output object T, all in the context of some effectful computation defined by the wander.

        Type Parameters:
        S - The input object type.
        T - The output object type.
        A - The input field type.
        B - The output field type.
        Parameters:
        wander - A mapping from effectful functions on the field types to effectful functions on the object types.
        input - A (non-effectful) transformation between object types.
        Returns:
        A transformation between object types.
        See Also:
        Wander, Traversable

      • traverse

        default <T extends K1,A,B> P<T<A>,T<B>> traverse(Traversable T traversable,
                                                 P<A,B> input)
        Takes a Traversable instance and some input transformation, and produces an output transformation between the effects defined by the traversable instance.

        This is a specialization of wander(Wander, App2) where S' = T<A> and T' = T<B>.

        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation calls wander(Wander, App2) with a Wander value that uses the given Traversable to traverse inputs.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The traversable type.
        A - The input field type.
        B - The output field type.
        Parameters:
        traversable - A Traversable instance for T.
        input - A transformation between field types.
        Returns:
        A transformation between effects of the field types.

      • first

        default <A,B,C> P<(A,C),(B,C)> first(P<A,B> input)
        Description copied from interface: Cartesian
        Converts the given transformation into one that transforms the first type of a Pair. The second type is not transformed - any values of that type are passed through the returned transformation unchanged.
        Specified by:
        first in interface Cartesian P extends K2
        Type Parameters:
        A - The input type.
        B - The output type.
        C - A "pass-through" type that is not transformed.
        Parameters:
        input - The transformation.
        Returns:
        A transformation on pairs, where the first type is transformed and the second is not.
